ed buffs from other classes.  Are haste items overkill?  I saw someone once say that a bard reaches max haste with just one haste item.  Does this mean a FBSS is about worthless on us?<br>
<br>
When I bother to pay attention to my damage during fights, usually concentrating on twisting those songs, I'm knicking the mobs for 20s, if that.  Yes, I have crude for weapons right now, Martuen Rapier and EBW.  Most places I hunt will not allow me to use my combat songs due to them being AE and having mezzed mobs nearby.<br>
<br>
I'm starting to think that I should hunt for an AC/STR belt for now.<br>
<br>
Opinions?<br>
<br>
Tatter D'Malion<br>
Bardette <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uchants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/5/00 10:24:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards and Haste</span><hr size=1> Bards get dual wield, as do monks, rogues, rangers and warriors.  Haste definately enhances this skill.<br>
<br>
Haste comes from two sources, an item or a spell/song.  Somethimes, the song/spell comes from an item, like the Wisteling Cloak or an executioner's axe.  But keep in mind that haste only comes from two sources.<br>
<br>
You can only benefit from one spell/song, and one item.  Therefore, If a bard is playing a haste its not quite beneficial for a shaman to speed the tanks.  It is also compeltely pointless to have a cloak of flames and a second haste item, like an FBSS since only one will benefit you.  Spells dont stack with other spells and items doent stack with other items.<br>
<br>
So unless a bard has a haste item, he will be missing out on close to half of the haste he may available to him.  For a class with dual wield, that's kind of a waste, in my opinion.  Bards unquestionably benefit from a haste item.<br>
<br>
Chants Evensong <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/5/00 12:35:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legendward/brink.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards and Haste</span><hr size=1> ...on the other hand Chants, bear in mind that dual wield or not, we're doing half of bugger all damage with weapons anyway.<br>
<br>
My weapons are Ebon Razor and Wraithbone Hammer, and I'm doing a 35 damage max to the mobs. Most of the time I'm doing 15-25.<br>
<br>
Compare that (at 47th) with 3x45 for Chant of Frost and Chant of Flame (each), and 3x28 for Fulfil's with a drum. With Selo's drum that's 3x61, 3x61, 3x38. (3x53, 3x53, 3x33 for MM Drums) (Plus 1-10 per punch woohoo!). (source - Rokenn's Site)<br>
<br>
All three chants are single target only.<br>
<br>
For me, you can keep your FBSS. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Brinklith Rioghbhardan</b> - Jester of Avalon<br>
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/mastersofavalon" target="_blank">Masters of Avalon</a><br>
Bard of Bristlebane<br>
<a href="http://www.brellserilis.net" target="_blank">Brell Serilis Server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uchants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/5/00 5:13:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards and Haste</span><hr size=1> Yes, I love to dot.  And I do it a lot.<br>
<br>
But it depends on my group and how I can make the group better.  In a group with 3 tanks, me, and no enchanter, I will whip out the vov and melee, and an fbss helps a lot.  <br>
<br>
The damage that I do with two dots (flame and frost with selo's drum) while twisting in vov is not much different from what I can do with weapons, vov and the dots unenhanced by a drum. <br>
<br>
I hit for a good amount.  Often more than 40. I have hit for 50+.  I am a significantly better fighter with an FBSS and I am glad to have that facet of my class preserved.  <br>
<br>
Chants <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ukalsyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalsyre</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/5/00 8:22:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards and Haste</span><hr size=1> I think haste items are semi-important for Bards.  It is true Bards can do quite abit of damage from twisting songs however, I dont think a Bard's primary responsibility in any group is to do the &quot;BIG Damage&quot; for the group.  Now Bards can do quite a bit of melee damage, just not as much as the other tank classes and haste does make a difference.<br>
<br>
A bard's goal should be to use his/her songs to assist the other members of the group which often means singing &quot;party beneficial&quot; songs instead of &quot;damage concentrating&quot; songs.  This drives my song selection and equipment selection more then damage output.  Besides, a Bard should never be 1 dimensional and should always be prepared for both songs and melee.  This means haste items are important.<br>
<br>
Now if you have a caster heavy group, then the bard debuff/dot songs can be very useful.  Or in Chants example a tank heavy group lends to VoV and Cantana.  <br>
<br>
I reccommend using something with AC (Troll Hide, TBB) over an fbss since I think the AC will benefit you more over the small haste in early levels, especially with the bard haste songs.  Of course idealy you should go for the POS Bard haste belt since it has stats, AC, and haste.<br>
<br>
Here is what I used over the levels (roughly)<br>
<br>
Level 5:  Purity Belt<br>
Level 21:  Troll Hide Belt<br>
Level 35:  Thick Banded Belt<br>
Level 50:  Belt of Concordance<br>
Level 55:  Thick Banded Belt (Cloak of Piety for Haste)<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 12:15:56 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legendward/brink.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards and Haste</span><hr size=1> Sorry, yeah - I was talking about when I'm damage-dealing. My guild leader's a mage, so I'm often partnering him with his pet. There's little I can do as far as buffing the pet (apart from Jonthan's II, but I'm not going to switch targets all the time!), so I'll stand back and use the heavy chants damage.<br>
