Bard of Bristlebane<br>
<a href="http://www.brellserilis.net" target="_blank">Brell Serilis Server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 2:02:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ..</span><hr size=1> personally i would rather use a AC belt than a FBSS...most groups i am using an instrument (string usually, heal, preservation, AE slow dot,VoV[singing]) (drum on dragons, and for using dots) ive punched for as much as 14 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  personally i think the bard is there to make everyone else look a lot better.... sometimes i break out weapons, but im not considering myself a tank or a high dmg dealer in any group (the dots are damn good tho).<br>
